# Chat Application

## Description

A real-time chat application that allows users to connect with friends, send messages, and manage friend requests. The application utilizes WebSockets for real-time communication and provides a user-friendly interface for managing chats and profiles.

## Features

- Real-time messaging with WebSocket support.
- Send and accept friend requests.
- User authentication and session management.
- Dynamic loading of friends and friend requests.
- Responsive design for mobile and desktop devices.

## Installation

1. Clone the repository:
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/LUZAmaxxp/chat-app.git
   ```
2. Navigate to the project directory:
   ```bash
   cd chat-app
   ```
3. Open the `client` directory and run the application:
   ```bash
   open index.html
   ```

## Usage

- Open the application in your web browser.
- Sign up for a new account or log in with existing credentials.
- Manage friend requests and start chatting with friends.

## Technologies Used

- HTML, CSS, JavaScript
- WebSocket for real-time communication
- Fetch API for handling HTTP requests

